    public class PNMLParser<P extends AbstractPlace<F,S>,T extends AbstractTransition<F,S>,F extends AbstractFlowRelation<P,T,S>,M extends AbstractMarking<S>,S,N extends AbstractPetriNet<P,T,F,M,S>,G extends AbstractPNGraphics<P,T,F,M,S>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PNParserInterface

    This class estimates the PNML type and chooses a fitting parser.

    The process of parsing a PNML file is the following:

    1. Check if the document is well-formed XML.
    2. Determine net type by reading the net type URI (get type from URINettypeRefs table).
    3. Read the net type specific net components. To avoid violating a constraint, the objects must be read in multiple iterations:
      1. Read nodes (places and transitions) with their marking and labeling.
      2. Read edges (arcs) with their annotations and specific starting and ending nodes.
    作者:
    Adrian Lange

        public AbstractGraphicalPN<P,T,F,M,S,N,G> parse(java.lang.String pnmlFile,
                                                boolean requireNetType,
                                                boolean verifySchema)
                                         throws java.io.IOException,
                                                de.invation.code.toval.parser.ParserException
        Parses a PNML File.
        参数:
        pnmlFile - File to parse
        requireNetType - Set to true if the net type should be required. If the net type can't be determined an exception will be thrown. If set to false, the parser will try to read the file as P/T-net.
        verifySchema - Set to true if the given file should be validated by the petri net type definition of the given file.
        返回:
        A AbstractGraphicalPN, acting as container for a petri net and its graphical information.
        抛出:
        java.io.IOException
        de.invation.code.toval.parser.ParserException
